  <div class="container">
    <h1><a href="index.html">| yesteryear forever |</a></h1>

    <blockquote>

      <p><strong>MOUND — Backyard Observatory</strong></p>

      <!-- -- LIVE DATA TEASER -- -->
      <div id="mound-teaser" style="border-left: 3px solid #2C3E50; padding: 0.8rem 1rem; margin: 1rem 0; font-size:0.9rem;">
        <p style="margin:0 0 0.4rem 0;">
          <strong>live — Central Ohio</strong>
          &nbsp;·&nbsp;
          <span id="mound-updated">loading...</span>
        </p>
        <p style="margin:0;">
          <span id="mound-temp">--</span>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;·&nbsp;&nbsp;
          <span id="mound-humidity">--</span>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;·&nbsp;&nbsp;
          <span id="mound-condition">--</span>
        </p>
        <p style="margin:0.5rem 0 0 0;">
          <a href="mound/index.html">&rarr; full sensor data, graphs, and archive</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <script>
        fetch('/mound/data/latest.json')
          .then(r => r.json())
          .then(d => {
            document.getElementById('mound-updated').textContent = 'last updated ' + d.updated;
            document.getElementById('mound-temp').textContent = d.temp;
            document.getElementById('mound-humidity').textContent = d.humidity;
            document.getElementById('mound-condition').textContent = d.condition;
          })
          .catch(() => {
            document.getElementById('mound-updated').textContent = 'data unavailable';
          });
      </script>

      <hr style="border:none; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

      <!-- -- INTRO -- -->
      <p>
        [YOUR INTRO PARAGRAPH HERE — set the scene. Something like: There is a small white tube
        standing in the garden behind my house on West Mound St. It has been there since late May 2026,
        quietly watching. It does not move. It does not speak. Every thirty minutes it takes the
        temperature, feels the humidity, checks the soil, measures the light, and sends a small
        report back to the house over WiFi. Then it goes back to watching.]
      </p>

      <p>
        [SECOND PARAGRAPH — the philosophy. The unmanned probe idea. Voyager. Sojourner.
        The beauty of sparse data. Why you love this kind of thing.]
      </p>

      <!-- -- FIRST IMAGE — float right -- -->
      <figure>
        <img src="images/mound_deployed_thumb.jpg"
             data-full="images/mound_deployed.jpg"
             alt="MOUND deployed in the garden"
             class="thumbnail align-right"
             loading="lazy">
        <figcaption>MOUND on its pole, first day outside.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p>
        [PARAGRAPH ABOUT THE NAME — West Mound St., the Ohio ancient culture naming tradition,
        Adena rover, Hopewell rockets. MOUND fits the family.]
      </p>

      <hr style="border:none; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

      <!-- -- HOW IT WORKS -- -->
      <p><strong>how it works</strong></p>

      <p>
        [BRIEF NON-TECHNICAL EXPLANATION — sensors listed simply. BME280 for temperature,
        humidity and pressure. TSL2591 for light. DS18B20 for soil temperature. Capacitive
        probe for soil moisture. Rain sensor. Pi camera. All wired to a Raspberry Pi Zero W
        running on a small solar panel and battery pack.]
      </p>

      <!-- -- SECOND IMAGE — float left -- -->
      <figure>
        <img src="images/mound_internals_thumb.jpg"
             data-full="images/mound_internals.jpg"
             alt="MOUND internals — perfboard and wiring"
             class="thumbnail align-left"
             loading="lazy">
        <figcaption>The perfboard — vestigial organs and all.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p>
        [PARAGRAPH ABOUT THE BUILD PROCESS — organic, tinkered, not perfectly engineered.
        The vestigial organs quote. The wire wrapping. The PVC housing. The toggle switch
        because of course there's a toggle switch.]
      </p>

      <p>
        [PARAGRAPH ABOUT THE SOLAR POWER — Waveshare charge controller, 18650 cells,
        the small panel. The experiment of it. What happens in November.]
      </p>

      <hr style="border:none; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

      <!-- -- THE DATA -- -->
      <p><strong>what it sees</strong></p>

      <p>
        [PARAGRAPH ABOUT THE DATA — what you've noticed so far. The humidity inversely
        mirroring temperature. Watching the sun rise in the lux graph. Soil temperature
        lagging hours behind air temperature. The pressure story. Waiting for Stacy to
        water the garden so you can see it in the soil moisture graph.]
      </p>

      <!-- -- SIDE BY SIDE — sample graph -- -->
      <figure>
        <img src="mound/graphs/today.png"
             alt="Sample MOUND sensor graph"
             style="width:100%; max-width:860px; display:block; margin: 0.5rem auto;"
             loading="lazy">
        <figcaption>A typical day — six sensor channels on a shared time axis.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p>
        [PARAGRAPH ABOUT WHAT YOU HOPE TO SEE OVER TIME — seasons changing, storms,
        the bat mic arriving from Japan, eventually a radio telescope. The long game.]
      </p>

      <hr style="border:none; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

      <!-- -- BUILD PHOTO GALLERY -- -->
      <p><strong>the build</strong></p>

      <div class="gallery">
        <img src="images/mound_01_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_01.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_02_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_02.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_03_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_03.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_04_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_04.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_05_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_05.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_06_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_06.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_07_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_07.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_08_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_08.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_09_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_09.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_10_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_10.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_11_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_11.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_12_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_12.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_13_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_13.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_14_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_14.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_15_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_15.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_16_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_16.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_17_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_17.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_18_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_18.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_19_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_19.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
        <img src="images/mound_20_thumb.jpg" data-full="images/mound_20.jpg" class="thumbnail" loading="lazy">
      </div>

      <hr style="border:none; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

      <!-- -- CLOSING -- -->
      <p>
        [CLOSING PARAGRAPH — something quiet and naturalist. The feeling of knowing something
        is out there watching even when you're not. The Desiderata angle maybe.
        The cosmos in a backyard on a Tuesday night in Ohio.]
      </p>

      <p><em>"[CLOSING QUOTE]"</em><br>
      — [ATTRIBUTION]</p>

      <hr style="border:none; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; margin: 1.5rem 0;">

      <p style="text-align:center;">
        <a href="mound/index.html">? live sensor data, graphs, and daily archive</a>
      </p>

    </blockquote>

    <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #999;">2026-05-31</p>

